<subSubSection id="5F07FEBC99828B84E8B67F1AF71F3067" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="0DE2543B1C08610774B817D0E5773D1C" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB49B9D71655A994E5FA607508E777F9" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Exclusively recorded from soft sediment habitats outside coral reefs. Depth 11-21 m.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ACC69949AA8F810397AAA889E7854D3F" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="96C5297343DE6D317546208E331D20A4" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0CF8935F58D5E57C5DB2086907127166" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
Widespread throughout the Indo-Pacific including the Red Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="B646669E5B47216FBE0D41C25BF82F44" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-662-45201-1_30" author="Yonow, N" editor="Rasul, NMA" journalOrPublisher="Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="531 - 550" refId="B289" refString="Yonow, N, 2015. Sea Slugs: unexpected biodiversity and distribution. In: Rasul, NMA, Stewart, ICF, Eds., The Red Sea. Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg: 531 - 550, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-662-45201-1_30" title="Sea Slugs: unexpected biodiversity and distribution." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-662-45201-1_30" volumeTitle="The Red Sea." year="2015">Yonow 2015</bibRefCitation>
), Mozambique (
<bibRefCitation id="45040B9E892FCFD2BEF304A5CB908A20" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4359.1.1" author="Tibirica, Y" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="1 - 133" refId="B252" refString="Tibirica, Y, Pola, M, Cervera, JL, 2017. Astonishing diversity revealed: an annotated and illustrated inventory of Nudipleura (Gastropoda: Heterobranchia) from Mozambique. Zootaxa 4359: 1 - 133, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4359.1.1" title="Astonishing diversity revealed: an annotated and illustrated inventory of Nudipleura (Gastropoda: Heterobranchia) from Mozambique." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4359.1.1" volume="4359" year="2017">
<normalizedToken id="2A2FF1A56C4DB9F12BC5529F972D3038" originalValue="Tibiriçá">Tibirica</normalizedToken>
et al. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
), India (
<bibRefCitation id="8A7B5BD37264928E197641DEA4253562" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11609/JoTT.o2783.2499-509" author="Sreeraj, CR" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Threatened Taxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="2499 - 2509" refId="B238" refString="Sreeraj, CR, Chandrakasan, S, Raghunathan, C, 2012. An annotated checklist of opisthobranch fauna (Gastropoda: Opisthobranchia) of the Nicobar Islands, India. Journal of Threatened Taxa 4: 2499 - 2509, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11609/JoTT.o2783.2499-509" title="An annotated checklist of opisthobranch fauna (Gastropoda: Opisthobranchia) of the Nicobar Islands, India." url="https://doi.org/10.11609/JoTT.o2783.2499-509" volume="4" year="2012">Sreeraj et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
), Maldives (
<bibRefCitation id="9B03E8CDEF457EF86B1D73C176736F57" author="Yonow, N" journalOrPublisher="Fauna of Saudi Arabia" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" refId="B282" refString="Yonow, N, 1994. Opisthobranchs from the Maldive Islands, including descriptions of seven new species (Mollusca: Gastropoda). Revue francaise d'aquariologie (1993) 20: 97-129." title="Opisthobranchs from the Maldive Islands, including descriptions of seven new species (Mollusca: Gastropoda). Revue francaise d'aquariologie (1993) 20: 97 - 129." year="1994">Yonow 1994</bibRefCitation>
), Tanzania, Mauritius, Indonesia, the Philippines, Taiwan, Australia, Papua New Guinea, Solomon Islands, Hawaii, and the Pacific coast of Mexico (
<bibRefCitation id="AE2FC49CF4976D89AA8B3B66BD871C21" author="Gosliner, TM" journalOrPublisher="Sea Challengers Natural History Books, Gig Harbor" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" refId="B94" refString="Gosliner, TM, Behrens, D, Valdes, A, 2008. Indo-Pacific nudibranchs and sea slugs: a field guide to the world's most diverse fauna. Sea Challengers Natural History Books, Gig Harbor" title="Indo-Pacific nudibranchs and sea slugs: a field guide to the world's most diverse fauna." year="2008">Gosliner et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="94CCCF07293A971A30B62D82FC58EAFD" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="54B6A48F627CD913A4CF9F6AB0FACBE5" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B8CB4D3C341DFD3AFB3A19EBC9A9F2E9" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
Individuals from Koh Tao have a dark, almost black mantle with numerous inconspicuous black spots. 
<taxonomicName id="7078B59214910BB8E92C445B3BC556EB" baseAuthorityName="Pilsbry" baseAuthorityYear="1896" class="Gastropoda" family="Pleurobranchidae" genus="Berthella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Berthella martensi" order="Pleurobranchida" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="martensi">
<emphasis id="696FB29D91598D09A23954F6DC1A45AB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Berthella martensi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded by 
<bibRefCitation id="105B0FB8314EED6BC622CA40FA66B223" author="Nabhitabhata, J" journalOrPublisher="Office of Natural Resources and Environmental Policy and Planning, Ministry of Natural Resources and Environment, Bangkok" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" refId="B171" refString="Nabhitabhata, J, 2009. Checklist of Mollusca Fauna in Thailand. Office of Natural Resources and Environmental Policy and Planning, Ministry of Natural Resources and Environment, Bangkok" title="Checklist of Mollusca Fauna in Thailand." year="2009">Nabhitabhata (2009)</bibRefCitation>
based on a local record (in Thai), but the location(s) of this record is unknown. Therefore, while 
<taxonomicName id="114EF3C95FD5C0D3520312D3C0CBA1BB" genus="B." lsidName="B. martensi" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="martensi">
<emphasis id="B2664305F8CAE8321BF36879873FDE25" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">B. martensi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from the Gulf of Thailand, its presence along the Andaman coast of Thailand is unconfirmed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
